-- tNotes on historical figures -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSelected Political Writings gathers Stuart Hall's best-known and most important essays that directly engage with political issues. Written between 1957 and 2011 and appearing in publications such as New Left Review and Marxism Today, these twenty essays span the whole of Hall's career, from his early involvement with the New Left, to his critique of Thatcherism, to his later focus on neoliberalism. Whether addressing economic decline and class struggle, the Cuban Missile Crisis, or the politics of empire, Hall's singular commentary and theorizations make this volume essential for anyone interested in the politics of the last sixty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aPolitical science. 0aPolitical sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / European.2bisacsh1 aDavison, Sally, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavison, Sally, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFeatherstone, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeatherstone, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRustin, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRustin, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchwarz, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwarz, Bill, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106963490 cprintz978082236386640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822372943?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372943423Coveruhttps://